rComments: Interesting lectures but really rude guy when talking one on one, I went in to get some feedback on my paper moving forward towards the exam and he told me I was either "a genius or the complete opposite."

Poetics was one of my most interesting yet most difficult courses. I am an A student and had to work really hard and follow up in office hours for papers to make sure that I scraped through. Lots of readings and many difficult concepts to understand, but he loves questions and is genuinely passionate about making sure students understand.
Prof Stacey was ok at best. Very sporadic in his lectures and not very clear about what his objectives are. But overall not an awful experience.
Course ENG 3111.  Amazing prof and very engaging with the class.  hard marker but always available for extra help and clarification.

Professor Stacey is all-around a great teacher, his grading is a little more difficult, however his feedback is really good. He is willing to talk with you one-on-one to discuss your grades and is very to the point with grading (which is nice). Make sure you stay up with the readings in his class because there are reading quizzes.

Dr. Stacey is probably my favorite prof so far! The course is entitled Literature, Madness and Desire, the course material that was chosen was so much fun to read! Class discussions were unfiltered, everyone was welcome to their opinion on controversial subjects and the last day, he asked the class for their opinion on the reading for the course.

Hands down one of the best english profs the university has to offer. I went in to the class expecting it to be dry because who really cares about Canadian literature? But he made the course content interesting while still acknowledging some realities of Canadian culture. Also gave lots of good feedback on essays and helped me get a better grade.

He was great. I don't understand why more people weren't into the class. The texts were interesting and the lectures were clear and pretty entertaining. This was one of the highlights of my year. He's super tough on essays though.
He was an okay prof. Seemed like he genuinely wants his students to do well. Does not answer his emails.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: he is the best and by far the most interesting prof I have ever had. He's a pretty hard marker but if you go to class and do your work you'll be fine. I don't even like english and I like his classes

attendance is mandatory, there is a sheet you need to sign, and if you want to pass, you better be in class because he only lectures, there is nothing he puts online so if you miss it - you miss it. lectures are usually really interesting, he does a great job keeping the attention of students! reallllly hard marker though, be careful on essays!

This is a fabulous course, taught with a great amount of enthusiasm which works contagious. Prof. Stacey is the right pilot to guide you through the, sometimes demanding texts, and bring you to a higher level in an interesting, engaging way. Very helpful during office hours, even gives more time if necessary. One of the best Profs I had so far!

My favourite prof. I wish he taught more classes so I could have him every year. Extremely helpful and passionate about everything he teaches. A fair marker, and an extremely nice person. Clearly explains concepts and his expectations. AMAZING!

Very enthusiastic. Not particularly helpful in office hours. Hard marker where essays are concerned and his feedback contradicted itself. Can be a little annoying in class ... makes up a lot of words and can be very repetitive.

Great Canadian Lit Seminar! Definitely one of my favourite English profs. He's so helpful and actually cares about students. His marking isn't ridiculous: if you work hard, you will be rewarded. He's really funny, too.

Perhaps because it was a summer course, I found his teaching structure to be disconnected. A little ADHD? It was obvious what content turned him on most, as he overlapped onto student presentations, essentially taking the wind out of their sails, so to speak. Maybe a little more experience in structuring lesson plans is in order.

Awesome Prof. So much fun and really conveys his love for the material. He likes to challenge his students by exposing them to new things (sound poetry?!). Loved him! He made my year. Highly recommended.

I thought that he was lots of fun, really interactive and made things interesting. Clearly interested in being a good teacher. He is a tough but very fair marker, and he gives lots of feedback. Exams are not stressful, one take home and one sit down but it wasnt long, and then there were two mid length papers. Not a crazy amount of reading either
funny, interesting lectures. easily one of my favourite profs. knows his stuff and conveys it effectively.
